  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "E. coli synthesizes purine and pyrimidine nucleotides de novo for DNA and RNA. Purine synthesis (10 steps) builds the ring on ribose-5-phosphate starting from PRPP, using amino acids (Gly, Gln, Asp) and one-carbon units from folate. Pyrimidine synthesis builds the ring first (UMP pathway, 6 steps), then attaches to ribose. Both pathways are regulated by feedback inhibition and transcriptional control. Salvage pathways recover preformed bases.",
  "id": "ecoli_nucleotide_biosynthesis",
  "keywords": [
    "nucleotide biosynthesis",
    "purine synthesis",
    "pyrimidine synthesis",
    "PRPP",
    "IMP",
    "UMP"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-15",
  "logicGates": {
    "and": 4,
    "not": 2,
    "or": 3
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    %% Entry Point\n    A[Ribose-5-Phosphate] --> B[\"PrsA: R5P + ATP \u2192 PRPP\"]\n    B --> C[PRPP Phosphoribosyl Pyrophosphate]\n    \n    %% OR Gate 1: Purine vs Pyrimidine\n    C --> D{OR: Which<br/>Nucleotide?}\n    D -->|Purines| E[Purine Biosynthesis]\n    D -->|Pyrimidines| F[Pyrimidine Biosynthesis]\n    \n    %% Purine Pathway Step-by-Step\n    E --> G[\"PurF: PRPP + Gln \u2192 5-Phosphoribosylamine\"]\n    G --> H[\"PurD: + Gly\"]\n    H --> I[GAR Glycinamide Ribotide]\n    I --> J[\"PurN: + Formyl-THF\"]\n    J --> K(\\1)\n    K --> L[\"PurL: + Gln\"]\n    L --> M(\\1)\n    M --> N[\"PurM: Cyclization\"]\n    N --> O[AIR 5-Aminoimidazole Ribotide]\n    O --> P[\"PurK: + CO2\"]\n    P --> Q(\\1)\n    Q --> R[\"PurE: + Asp\"]\n    R --> S(\\1)\n    S --> T[\"PurB: Release Fumarate\"]\n    T --> U(\\1)\n    U --> V[\"PurH: + Formyl-THF\"]\n    V --> W(\\1)\n    W --> X[\"PurH: Cyclization\"]\n    X --> Y[IMP Inosine Monophosphate]\n    \n    %% IMP Branch Point\n    Y --> Z{OR: AMP<br/>or GMP?}\n    Z -->|PurA| AA[IMP + Asp + GTP \u2192 AMP]\n    Z -->|PurB+GuaA| AB[IMP + NAD \u2192 GMP]\n    \n    AA --> AC[AMP Adenosine Monophosphate]\n    AB --> AD[GMP Guanosine Monophosphate]\n    \n    %% Pyrimidine Pathway\n    F --> AE[\"CarAB: Gln + CO2 + ATP \u2192 Carbamoyl-P\"]\n    AE --> AF[\"PyrB: Carbamoyl-P + Asp\"]\n    AF --> AG[Carbamoyl Aspartate]\n    AG --> AH[\"PyrC: Cyclization\"]\n    AH --> AI[Dihydroorotate DHO]\n    AI --> AJ[\"PyrD: DHO + NAD \u2192 Orotate\"]\n    AJ --> AK(\\1)\n    AK --> AL[\"PyrE: Orotate + PRPP \u2192 Orotidine-5-P\"]\n    AL --> AM[Orotidine Monophosphate]\n    AM --> AN[\"PyrF: Decarboxylation\"]\n    AN --> AO[UMP Uridine Monophosphate]\n    \n    %% UMP to CTP\n    AO --> AP[\"PyrH: UMP + ATP \u2192 UDP\"]\n    AP --> AQ(\\1)\n    AQ --> AR[\"Ndk: UDP + ATP \u2192 UTP\"]\n    AR --> AS(\\1)\n    AS --> AT[\"PyrG: UTP + Gln + ATP \u2192 CTP\"]\n    AT --> AU[CTP Cytidine Triphosphate]\n    \n    %% Nucleoside Diphosphate Kinase\n    AC --> AV[AMP \u2192 ADP \u2192 ATP]\n    AD --> AW[GMP \u2192 GDP \u2192 GTP]\n    \n    AV --> AX{AND: ATP<br/>Levels?}\n    AW --> AY{AND: GTP<br/>Levels?}\n    AS --> AZ{AND: UTP<br/>Levels?}\n    AU --> BA{AND: CTP<br/>Levels?}\n    \n    %% Ribonucleotide Reductase\n    AX -->|Sufficient| BB[\"RNR: ATP \u2192 dATP\"]\n    AY -->|Sufficient| BC[\"RNR: GTP \u2192 dGTP\"]\n    AZ -->|Sufficient| BD[\"RNR: UTP \u2192 dUTP\"]\n    BA -->|Sufficient| BE[\"RNR: CTP \u2192 dCTP\"]\n    \n    BD --> BF[\"Dut: dUTP \u2192 dUMP\"]\n    BF --> BG[\"ThyA: dUMP + CH2-THF \u2192 dTMP\"]\n    BG --> BH[dTMP \u2192 dTDP \u2192 dTTP]\n    \n    %% DNA/RNA Synthesis\n    BB --> BI(\\1)\n    BC --> BJ(\\1)\n    BE --> BK(\\1)\n    BH --> BL(\\1)\n    \n    BI --> BM{OR: DNA<br/>or RNA?}\n    BJ --> BM\n    BK --> BM\n    BL --> BM\n    AV --> BM\n    AW --> BM\n    AS --> BM\n    AU --> BM\n    \n    BM -->|DNA| BN[DNA Polymerase]\n    BM -->|RNA| BO[RNA Polymerase]\n    \n    BN --> BP([DNA Replication])\n    BO --> BQ([Transcription])\n    \n    %% Feedback Regulation\n    AC --> BR[/PurR Repressor/]\n    BR --> BS[/pur Operon Repression/]\n    \n    AO --> BT[PyrR Attenuation]\n    BT --> BU[pyr Operon Control]\n    \n    %% Salvage Pathways\n    BV(\\1) --> BW[\"Apt: + PRPP \u2192 AMP\"]\n    BW --> AC\n    BX(\\1) --> BY[\"Gpt: + PRPP \u2192 GMP\"]\n    BY --> AD\n    BZ(\\1) --> CA[\"Upp: + PRPP \u2192 UMP\"]\n    CA --> AO\n    \n    %% Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style B fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style G fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style H fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style I fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style J fill:#b3e5fc,color: